tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE student_mobility_data (
  student_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  program_id INT,
  study_abroad_country VARCHAR(50),
  academic_performance_rating INT,
  career_outcomes_rating INT
)

CREATE TABLE student (
    student_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    student_name VARCHAR(255),
    current_program VARCHAR(255),
    study_abroad_program VARCHAR(255)
);

CREATE TABLE mobility_data (
    data_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    student_id INT,
    semester INT,
    academic_performance VARCHAR(255),
    career_outcomes VARCHAR(255)
)

CREATE TABLE students (
    student_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    first_name TEXT NOT NULL,
    last_name TEXT NOT NULL,
    email TEXT UNIQUE NOT NULL,
    date_of_birth DATE
);

CREATE TABLE study_abroad_programs (
    program_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    program_name TEXT NOT NULL,
    country TEXT NOT NULL,
    start_date DATE,
    end_date DATE
);

CREATE TABLE student_outcomes (
    outcome_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    student_id UUID REFERENCES students(student_id),
    program_id UUID REFERENCES study_abroad_programs(program_id),
    gpa FLOAT,
    job_placement BOOLEAN
);

CREATE TABLE Students (
    student_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    student_name VARCHAR(50),
    gender VARCHAR(10),
    dob DATE,
    home_country VARCHAR(50),
    study_program VARCHAR(50)
);

CREATE TABLE StudyAbroadPrograms (
    program_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    program_name VARCHAR(50),
    program_duration INT,
    host_country VARCHAR(50),
    program_type VARCHAR(20)
);

CREATE TABLE CourseGrades (
    grade_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    student_id INT,
    course_name VARCHAR(50),
    grade VARCHAR(2),
    semester VARCHAR(20)
);

CREATE TABLE CareerOutcomes (
    outcome_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    student_id INT,
    job_title VARCHAR(50),
    employer VARCHAR(50),
    salary DECIMAL(10, 2)
);
